  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAfter 15 Peepeth posts by default, but even less if the user desires so, peeps need to be saved to the blockchain. After a certain threshold users are allowed to save peeps to the blockchain for free, they just need to sign the transaction.\r\n\r\nIf the message is dismissed it can be accessed again via the red link reading \"Save 15 actions\" in the bottom left corner shown below.\r\n\r\n![screen0](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/457281/43666316-058050ae-977c-11e8-9863-9d76a0997f8b.jpg)\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: After 15 peeps user is presented with a screen that asks the user to sign the transaction and a hash message is displayed.\r\n\r\n![screen1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/457281/43650845-8416474e-9749-11e8-8c86-1b223de7988d.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nOnce the \"Sign now\" button is pressed on the screen above, user is taken into a sign transaction window (image below), password needs to be introduced and transaction is to be signed. After signing, user is brought back to Peepeth website.\r\n\r\n![screen2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/457281/43650844-83f76ed2-9749-11e8-893c-75ff43a79baf.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nOnce the sign transaction button is pressed, user is taken into a sign transaction window, password is introduced and Sign button is pressed, BUT user is returned again to the screen with 'Sign now' button.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nAfter reaching a threshold of 15 peeps posted, Peepeth will ask you to save your posts to the blockchain. Presuming you have freepeeping allowed (50 peeps posted or Twitter/Github account verified), follow the steps bellow to reproduce the bug:\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Locate Peepeth in dApps directory\r\n- Sign into it\r\n- Peepeth will ask you to sign the transaction that will authorize saving the peeps onto the blockchain, so press 'Sign now' button\r\n- Enter your Status wallet password\r\n- Press Sign\r\n\r\nIf the bug still exists, you will be again on the 'Sign now' screen.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: tested and reproduced on the latest nightly \r\n* Operating System: Tested on one Android 6.0.1 (rooted) and 2 different 7.0 devices (rooted and non-rooted), all producing the same loop-back to 'Sign now' page\r\n* Transaction signing is successfully done once every time users access Peepeth, as they need to sign in from their wallet address, and that part works well from all 3 tested Status versions and all 3 Android phones mentioned above\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n[logcat.txt](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2258835/logcat.txt)\r\n",
